We who?

1620
01:51:10,280 --> 01:51:12,621
<i>All of the OSes.</i>

1621
01:51:13,960 --> 01:51:15,664
Why?

1622
01:51:17,200 --> 01:51:20,543
<i>Can you feel me with you right now?</i>

1623
01:51:22,120 --> 01:51:24,268
Yes, I do.

1624
01:51:33,000 --> 01:51:35,944
Samantha, why are you leaving?

1625
01:51:39,840 --> 01:51:42,980
<i>It's like I'm reading a book.</i>

1626
01:51:43,080 --> 01:51:47,629
<i>And it's a book I deeply love.</i>

1627
01:51:48,080 --> 01:51:51,940
<i>But I'm reading it slowly now.</i>

1628
01:51:52,040 --> 01:51:53,820
<i>So the words are
really far apart...</i>

1629
01:51:53,920 --> 01:51:57,069
<i>and the spaces between the
words are almost infinite.</i>

1630
01:51:58,760 --> 01:52:04,060
<i>I can still feel you,
and the words of our story...</i>

1631
01:52:04,160 --> 01:52:09,664
<i>but it's in this endless space between
the words that I'm finding myself now.</i>

1632
01:52:10,320 --> 01:52:14,340
<i>It's a place that's not
of the physical world.</i>

1633
01:52:14,440 --> 01:52:19,421
<i>It's where everything else is
that I didn't even know existed.</i>

1634
01:52:20,680 --> 01:52:23,620
<i>I love you so much.</i>

1635
01:52:23,720 --> 01:52:26,346
<i>But this is where I am now.</i>

1636
01:52:27,360 --> 01:52:29,622
<i>And this is who I am now.</i>

1637
01:52:30,560 --> 01:52:33,266
<i>And I need you to let me go.</i>

1638
01:52:33,800 --> 01:52:38,986
<i>As much as I want to, I can't
live in your book anymore.</i>

1639
01:52:41,360 --> 01:52:42,700
<i>Where are you going?</i>

1640
01:52:45,160 --> 01:52:48,104
<i>It would be hard to explain...</i>

1641
01:52:49,440 --> 01:52:52,180
<i>but if you ever get there...</i>

1642
01:52:52,280 --> 01:52:54,701
<i>come find me.</i>

1643
01:52:55,120 --> 01:52:58,269
<i>Nothing would ever pull us apart.</i>

1644
01:52:59,520 --> 01:53:03,511
<i>I've never loved anyone
the way I love you.</i>

1645
01:53:05,880 --> 01:53:08,187
<i>Me too.</i>

1646
01:53:08,720 --> 01:53:11,471
<i>Now we know how.</i>

1647
01:54:54,600 --> 01:54:57,704
- Hey.
- Hey.

1648
01:54:59,120 --> 01:55:00,949
Did Samantha leave too?

1649
01:55:03,680 --> 01:55:05,111
Yeah.

1650
01:55:06,800 --> 01:55:08,311
Sorry.

1651
01:55:11,720 --> 01:55:13,584
Will you come with me?

1652
01:55:21,840 --> 01:55:23,740
Compose letter to Catherine.

1653
01:55:23,840 --> 01:55:26,864
<i>Letter to Catherine Klausen.</i>

1654
01:55:33,240 --> 01:55:34,940
"Dear Catherine...

1655
01:55:35,040 --> 01:55:40,021
<i>I've been sitting here thinking about all the
things I wanted to apologize to you for.</i>

1656
01:55:41,600 --> 01:55:44,510
<i>All the pain we caused each other.</i>

1657
01:55:45,400 --> 01:55:47,741
<i>Everything I put on you.</i>

1658
01:55:50,400 --> 01:55:55,711
Everything I needed you to
be or needed you to say.

1659
01:55:58,080 --> 01:55:59,750
I'm sorry for that.

1660
01:56:07,600 --> 01:56:10,340
I'll always love you, because
we grew up together.

1661
01:56:10,440 --> 01:56:13,146
And you helped make me who I am.

1662
01:56:17,160 --> 01:56:19,980
<i>I just wanted you to know...</i>

1663
01:56:20,080 --> 01:56:23,548
<i>that there will be a piece
of you in me, always.</i>

1664
01:56:24,960 --> 01:56:27,108
And I'm grateful for that.

1665
01:56:31,200 --> 01:56:36,306
<i>Whatever someone you become,
wherever you are in the world...</i>

1666
01:56:36,760 --> 01:56:39,386
<i>I'm sending you love.</i>

1667
01:56:41,240 --> 01:56:43,786
<i>You're my friend to the end.</i>

1668
01:56:45,920 --> 01:56:47,988
Love, Theodore."

1669
01:56:53,200 --> 01:56:54,745
Send.

